(97, 1, '2015-02-16 08:19:42', '2015-02-16 08:19:42', 'This is an example page. It''s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I''m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin'' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://localhost/raceit/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!', 'Sample Page', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-16 08:19:42', '2015-02-16 08:19:42', '', 2, 'http://localhost/raceit/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(98, 1, '2015-02-16 08:20:47', '2015-02-16 08:20:47', 'While Race IT provides a personalized experience, we are committed to safeguarding our users'' privacy, especially the privacy of our child users. (For the purposes of this policy a child is a person 12 years of age or younger).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRace IT is compliant with the Children''s Online Privacy Protection Act, otherwise known as COPPA. We have posted our Children''s privacy policy to help both children and parents understand how a child''s personal information will be treated as they interact with our registration system and tools. This policy may be modified from time to time to better address your concerns or to reflect new changes in online policy, so please check back frequently.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor more detailed information on COPPA, please visit: http://www.coppa.org/coppa.htm\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWho collects information?\r\nInformation is collected from children on the Race IT registration environment. Race IT is a Limited Liability Corporation located at:\r\n\r\n9030 Stony Point Pkwy Suite 450\r\nRichmond, VA 23235\r\n866-972-2348\r\ninformation@RaceIT.com\r\n\r\nWhat kind of personal information is collected and how is it used?\r\nRace IT will not collect personal information about you or your child unless you provide it to us or publicly post it voluntarily and knowingly. We respect the privacy of children, and do not collect any more personal information than is necessary to enable them to participate in the activities we offer at our Web site. However, in order to register for leagues and events, you will be asked to provide registration data through an online registration form. The information collected may include you or your child''s legal name, address, telephone number, email address, and birth date.\r\n\r\nWe will not sell or rent your child''s information to third parties at all, ever, under any circumstances. If you or your child has submitted personal information to us and would like to change it or remove it from our records, simply contact us at information@RaceIT.com and we will delete the information.\r\n\r\nWe do not share children’s personal information with anyone other than those who fulfill the registrations performed via our web site (e.g., league administrators, race directors).\r\n\r\nParental Review\r\nParents can review the information that we have collected from their children online, prevent the further use or maintenance of such information, or direct the deletion of their children’s personal information by:\r\n\r\ncalling us at the telephone number provided above\r\ne-mailing us at the above address\r\nwriting to us at the above address\r\ninformation@RaceIT.com', 'Child Privacy Policy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '82-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-16 08:20:47', '2015-02-16 08:20:47', '', 82, 'http://localhost/raceit/82-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(99, 1, '2015-02-16 08:21:36', '2015-02-16 08:21:36', '<p>While Race IT provides a personalized experience, we are committed to safeguarding our users'' privacy, especially the privacy of our child users. (For the purposes of this policy a child is a person 12 years of age or younger).\r\n\r\nRace IT is compliant with the Children''s Online Privacy Protection Act, otherwise known as COPPA. We have posted our Children''s privacy policy to help both children and parents understand how a child''s personal information will be treated as they interact with our registration system and tools. This policy may be modified from time to time to better address your concerns or to reflect new changes in online policy, so please check back frequently.\r\n\r\nFor more detailed information on COPPA, please visit: http://www.coppa.org/coppa.htm\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWho collects information?\r\nInformation is collected from children on the Race IT registration environment. Race IT is a Limited Liability Corporation located at:\r\n\r\n9030 Stony Point Pkwy Suite 450\r\nRichmond, VA 23235\r\n866-972-2348\r\ninformation@RaceIT.com\r\n\r\nWhat kind of personal information is collected and how is it used?\r\nRace IT will not collect personal information about you or your child unless you provide it to us or publicly post it voluntarily and knowingly. We respect the privacy of children, and do not collect any more personal information than is necessary to enable them to participate in the activities we offer at our Web site. However, in order to register for leagues and events, you will be asked to provide registration data through an online registration form. The information collected may include you or your child''s legal name, address, telephone number, email address, and birth date.\r\n\r\nWe will not sell or rent your child''s information to third parties at all, ever, under any circumstances. If you or your child has submitted personal information to us and would like to change it or remove it from our records, simply contact us at information@RaceIT.com and we will delete the information.\r\n\r\nWe do not share children’s personal information with anyone other than those who fulfill the registrations performed via our web site (e.g., league administrators, race directors).\r\n\r\nParental Review\r\nParents can review the information that we have collected from their children online, prevent the further use or maintenance of such information, or direct the deletion of their children’s personal information by:\r\n\r\ncalling us at the telephone number provided above\r\ne-mailing us at the above address\r\nwriting to us at the above address\r\ninformation@RaceIT.com', 'Child Privacy Policy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '82-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-16 08:21:36', '2015-02-16 08:21:36', '', 82, 'http://localhost/raceit/82-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
